Whether in the garden, on the balcony or on the terrace.Handmade from spruce wood and glued with waterproof wood glue and nailed.The birdhouse was first painted with acrylic paint and a lot of love, then made weatherproof with clear varnish, so that you will enjoy it for as long as possible.The "interior" is, in the sense of birds, untreated.For cleaning, the base (bottom plate) can be easily unscrewed and thus allows generous access to the interior.For mounting, a hole is drilled into the back, so you can simply hang it on a nail.The cottage is 39 cm high, 20 cm wide and 16 cm deep.If you would like to have something individual, please contact me.

name: Black Trans Lives Matter Resin Art Wallhanging for Charity
description: 60% of the proceeds from these items will be donated to the "ForTheGworlsParty" Project, which supports Black Trans People in the United States with funds for rent and gender affirming surgeries (more information, donation, and applications ot the fund here: https://linktr.ee/FORTHEGWORLSPARTY).I will be taking commisions for remakes of these pieces of which also 50% of the proceeds will be donated to this cause.Please accept my sincerest apologies for the prohibitively high shipping rates to the US - unfortunately there is nothing I can do to lower these costs as I am based in Europe. I am however also working on jewellery pieces that will have much lower shipping to the US. In the meantime, please consider donating to ForTheGworls or other causes that support black trans women.This is a completely handmade item, meaning that there may be some small imperfections - these add to the uniqueness of the product!Thank you so much for visiting my shop and for your interest in these items! If you like what you see here but would be interested in a slightly different variation feel free to send me a message and I can create a custom piece for you.You can also find me on Instagram @galloping_gargoyles_artTikTok @galloping_gargoylesEmail  gallopinggargoylesart [!at] gmail.com

name: Tarot resin art storage box "The Magician"
description: This box is made completely from epoxy resin. Into the lid a painted tarot card representing the magician is inlayed, and in the bottom of the box a painted skull is inlayed. The lid is transparent, meaning that you can see some of the inside the box when it is closed.Dimensions:Outer height with lid: 6.9cm (lid thickness: 1cm)Outer width: 9.5cmOuter length: 12.5cmInner height: 4cm without lid, 3.7cm with lidInner width: 7.5cmInner length: 10.5cmNotes on this item:The surface of the lid is even and smooth but there are some small irregularities on the edges of the surface. On the bottom of the lid (the side facing the inside of the box) there is one "bump" (visible in the last picture) where the surface is not even. This is where I filled a bubble in the casting!The bottom of the box (as can be seen in the last picture) is not completely regular. This is hardly noticeable when the box is the right way round and does not affect the inside.As with most resin cast objects there are a few small air bubbles on the surface of the box. These are mostly on the bottom edge and don't detract from the overall appearance.This is a completely handmade item, meaning that there may be some small imperfections - these add to the uniqueness of the product!Thank you so much for visiting my shop and for your interest in these items! If you like what you see here but would be interested in a slightly different variation feel free to send me a message and I can create a custom piece for you.You can also find me on Instagram @galloping_gargoyles_artTikTok @galloping_gargoylesEmail  gallopinggargoylesart [!at] gmail.com

description: Simple and reusable makeshift mask for everyday use.Made entirely of cotton, with elastic bands for wearing and opening for a filter.There are different possibilities for cleaning:Cooking potIf you don't want to start a machine for one or more masks, you can also boil the mask for at least five minutes in a saucepan with water and a pinch of detergent. This is the quick method, so to speak. To determine the correct temperature, you can use a kitchen or grill thermometer. Once the masks are boiled, you should let them dry well.KettlePour hot water from the kettle at a temperature of at least 70 °C into a pot or heat-resistant bowl. Put the mask in for five minutes, stirring it from time to time with a wooden spoon. Then take it out, lay it out on a towel and let it dry well.These masks are neither a medical product nor protective equipment.Proper handling is therefore important and is strongly recommended.Colors may vary depending on the device.
